00:20:22.574 --> 00:20:23.990
So I just wanted
to know how you--

00:20:23.990 --> 00:20:24.720
MANOJ BAJPAYEE:
Yeah, my director

00:20:24.720 --> 00:20:26.970
wanted to do see as to
how I'm going to dance.

00:20:26.970 --> 00:20:29.400
I said, please don't do it.

00:20:29.400 --> 00:20:32.490
You just switch on the camera,
say action, I'll do it.

00:20:32.490 --> 00:20:39.210
But it was a constable
who is constantly

00:20:39.210 --> 00:20:43.200
getting pressurized by the
day to day life, the pressures

00:20:43.200 --> 00:20:44.370
of the day to day life.

00:20:44.370 --> 00:20:47.730
And he doesn't know
how to deal with it.

00:20:47.730 --> 00:20:51.120
So this is the only way
he could just let it go.

00:20:51.120 --> 00:20:53.640
[LAUGHTER]

00:20:55.360 --> 00:21:00.510
If you have seen the film, he's
about to have brain hemorrhage.

00:21:00.510 --> 00:21:03.510
If he'll not dance it out, he
will have a brain hemorrhage,

00:21:03.510 --> 00:21:05.850
because he is getting
pressure from his duty,

00:21:05.850 --> 00:21:07.670
getting pressure from his wife--

00:21:07.670 --> 00:21:09.770
all of those things
are going on.

00:21:09.770 --> 00:21:15.450
And he doesn't know how to
just sort out his own life.

00:21:15.450 --> 00:21:20.520
And there comes this situation
where he just starts dancing.

00:21:20.520 --> 00:21:23.130
And after this, everything
gets sorted out.

00:21:23.130 --> 00:21:23.842
[LAUGHING]

00:21:23.842 --> 00:21:25.050
SPEAKER 1: He gets suspended.

00:21:25.050 --> 00:21:28.080
MANOJ BAJPAYEE: [LAUGHING]

00:21:28.080 --> 00:21:30.540
SPEAKER 1: So life is back.

00:21:30.540 --> 00:21:32.580
On the other end
of the spectrum,

00:21:32.580 --> 00:21:34.290
your character in
"Zubeidaa," which

00:21:34.290 --> 00:21:37.380
was based on a royal family--

00:21:37.380 --> 00:21:39.610
MANOJ BAJPAYEE: I will
never say it on record.

00:21:39.610 --> 00:21:41.220
SPEAKER 1: OK.

00:21:41.220 --> 00:21:43.920
It was inspired, I should say.

00:21:43.920 --> 00:21:46.140
That is something
rooted in history,

00:21:46.140 --> 00:21:51.810
and it had this grandeur and
this sort of stoicism to it.

00:21:51.810 --> 00:21:56.200
How did you feel doing
a movie like that?

00:21:56.200 --> 00:21:59.850
MANOJ BAJPAYEE: Yeah, it was
difficult. Because Shyam Bapu,

00:21:59.850 --> 00:22:01.020
I wanted to work with him.

00:22:01.020 --> 00:22:04.960
He's such a legendary
director of our country,

00:22:04.960 --> 00:22:08.670
after the late [NON-ENGLISH].

00:22:08.670 --> 00:22:11.280
And so many films
of his really--

00:22:11.280 --> 00:22:17.810
they left such an impact on
me when I was doing theater,

00:22:17.810 --> 00:22:21.360
or when I was growing
up in my small town.

00:22:21.360 --> 00:22:25.390
Those were the films, but they
were hardly available anywhere.

00:22:25.390 --> 00:22:28.630
One show somewhere in
[NON-ENGLISH] in Delhi.

00:22:28.630 --> 00:22:32.330
So you have to change
to two or three buses

00:22:32.330 --> 00:22:35.580
to reach on time for the film.

00:22:35.580 --> 00:22:37.530
But somehow you manage to do it.

00:22:37.530 --> 00:22:43.920
And those films have really
inspired not only me,

00:22:43.920 --> 00:22:48.180
but all the actors who were
doing theater those days.

00:22:48.180 --> 00:22:51.500
So it was a dream come true.

00:22:51.500 --> 00:22:55.020
And when he narrated
the role to me, I said,

00:22:55.020 --> 00:22:56.320
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

00:23:00.090 --> 00:23:02.980
So he said, first
of all, this role

00:23:02.980 --> 00:23:05.156
was rejected by all the stars.

00:23:05.156 --> 00:23:07.470
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

00:23:07.470 --> 00:23:10.880
And soon, I don't have any
other choice but to take you.

00:23:15.360 --> 00:23:18.350
But to keep you at
ease, I must tell you

00:23:18.350 --> 00:23:23.060
that this is the photograph
of the prince on whose life it

00:23:23.060 --> 00:23:24.055
is based on.

00:23:24.055 --> 00:23:25.430
Tell me who is
more good-looking.

00:23:25.430 --> 00:23:28.895
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

00:23:32.360 --> 00:23:34.430
I said, definitely,
that gives me arrogance

00:23:34.430 --> 00:23:37.370
to say that, yes, I'm much
more good-looking than him!

00:23:37.370 --> 00:23:41.510
So he said, OK, so
you've got your answer.

00:23:41.510 --> 00:23:44.660
The one thing that
he wanted me to--

00:23:44.660 --> 00:23:50.300
apart from learning
horseriding and learning polo--

00:23:50.300 --> 00:23:52.510
that was a physically
tough thing,

00:23:52.510 --> 00:23:53.870
but one could easily do it.

00:23:53.870 --> 00:23:57.950
For two months, three months
of practice, I have done it.

00:23:57.950 --> 00:24:00.080
But the most
difficult thing was I

00:24:00.080 --> 00:24:03.680
was born in a farmer's family,
middle class farmer's family.

00:24:03.680 --> 00:24:05.630
I've never been to any palace.

00:24:05.630 --> 00:24:09.530
I've never known any
princely state people.

00:24:09.530 --> 00:24:14.050
So I didn't know their behavior
pattern and their mental state.

00:24:14.050 --> 00:24:16.400
But some way, Shyam Bapu
has thought it out for me.

00:24:16.400 --> 00:24:21.570
He said, for a prince,
he takes it for granted

00:24:21.570 --> 00:24:25.460
that anybody who'll come to
him will bow down before him.

00:24:25.460 --> 00:24:31.460
So you have it in your mind.

00:24:31.460 --> 00:24:36.290
Since the time you were
born, in that kind of family,

00:24:36.290 --> 00:24:38.809
you know that if
you get into Google,

00:24:38.809 --> 00:24:40.850
the Google chairman will
be there to receive you.

00:24:40.850 --> 00:24:43.580
This is something
which is granted.

00:24:43.580 --> 00:24:46.890
This is not something that
you are going to think about.

00:24:46.890 --> 00:24:49.510
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] I'll
definitely think about

00:24:49.510 --> 00:24:50.910
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

00:24:55.270 --> 00:24:59.360
I mean, that prince will--
when he will come here,

00:24:59.360 --> 00:25:01.760
people will naturally
come to see him.

00:25:01.760 --> 00:25:03.420
People naturally
go to welcome him.

00:25:07.390 --> 00:25:11.256
This is what decides
their behavior pattern.

00:25:11.256 --> 00:25:15.410
So to get into the
zone of a prince's mind

00:25:15.410 --> 00:25:16.850
was a difficult, difficult part.

00:25:16.850 --> 00:25:21.550
Because my body language--
it was never of a prince.

00:25:21.550 --> 00:25:24.980
It was never up
of a feudal lord.

00:25:24.980 --> 00:25:26.960
Again, because I've
never seen them,

00:25:26.960 --> 00:25:30.500
never sat with them,
never had dinner with them

00:25:30.500 --> 00:25:31.820
or lunch with them.

00:25:31.820 --> 00:25:37.760
So to really get into the
mental zone of that character

00:25:37.760 --> 00:25:41.420
was very, very difficult.
But somehow, Shyam Bapu has

00:25:41.420 --> 00:25:45.567
helped me quite a lot
through all the shooting.

00:25:45.567 --> 00:25:47.400
