00:25:58.725 --> 00:26:02.400
MANOJ BAJPAYEE: Actually, "Love
Sonia" is not an English film.

00:26:02.400 --> 00:26:04.680
I've done two films--

00:26:04.680 --> 00:26:10.902
they are produced and directed
by the people who are LA-based.

00:26:10.902 --> 00:26:13.530
"Love Sonia" is one
and "In the Shadows."

00:26:13.530 --> 00:26:15.670
"In the Shadows" is
a film that I'm very,

00:26:15.670 --> 00:26:23.390
very proud of, because
it shot in [NON-ENGLISH]..

00:26:23.390 --> 00:26:27.770
And I would say that it's
the best film of my career,

00:26:27.770 --> 00:26:28.730
"In the Shadows."

00:26:28.730 --> 00:26:31.597
And according to me, that
is my best performance.

00:26:31.597 --> 00:26:33.680
People keep asking, what
is your best performance?

00:26:33.680 --> 00:26:34.930
What is your best performance?

00:26:34.930 --> 00:26:38.360
Somewhere, when the screening
was over of "In the Shadows,"

00:26:38.360 --> 00:26:45.890
and I said, yes, finally, I give
myself some marks as an actor.

00:26:45.890 --> 00:26:48.590
Because when you are
watching your own film--

00:26:48.590 --> 00:26:50.300
while people are
enjoying it, enjoying

00:26:50.300 --> 00:26:52.040
your performance,
but as an actor,

00:26:52.040 --> 00:26:54.930
you are always looking
at it differently.

00:26:54.930 --> 00:26:57.230
You are looking at
it very technically.

00:26:57.230 --> 00:27:00.930
And an actor can't
tell lies to himself.

00:27:00.930 --> 00:27:04.760
He's always thinking, I
could do better in that line.

00:27:04.760 --> 00:27:08.880
I could do a little
better in that sequence.

00:27:08.880 --> 00:27:10.190
So actor is never satisfied.

00:27:10.190 --> 00:27:15.110
But "In the Shadows" is a film
where not only I was pretty

00:27:15.110 --> 00:27:19.100
much taken aback by the craft
of the director and the story

00:27:19.100 --> 00:27:22.160
writer, but also,
yes, I was quite happy

00:27:22.160 --> 00:27:24.380
with my own performance.

00:27:24.380 --> 00:27:26.340
So, yes, I'm in "Love
Sonia" as the guy--

00:27:26.340 --> 00:27:28.070
I didn't want to
do that character,

00:27:28.070 --> 00:27:31.100
because it was very
discomforting for me

00:27:31.100 --> 00:27:33.110
to play a brothel keeper.

00:27:33.110 --> 00:27:39.840
Somebody who's initiating the
lead, who is a virgin girl--

00:27:39.840 --> 00:27:46.120
she's gotten into
big city like Bombay.

00:27:46.120 --> 00:27:50.590
And straight away, she was
put into this brothel, which

00:27:50.590 --> 00:27:51.820
I'm owning.

00:27:51.820 --> 00:27:55.510
And this guy is a ruthless guy,
but he talks very sweetly--

00:27:55.510 --> 00:27:56.740
very sweetly, he talks.

00:27:56.740 --> 00:28:01.420
And he gets this girl
to do the stuff, which

00:28:01.420 --> 00:28:03.800
is so, so scary for them.

00:28:03.800 --> 00:28:05.980
But he makes it easy for them.

00:28:05.980 --> 00:28:08.270
But he's dangerous, also--
very, very dangerous.

00:28:08.270 --> 00:28:11.620
If you go against his
rules, against him,

00:28:11.620 --> 00:28:14.350
then you will see hell.

00:28:14.350 --> 00:28:16.420
All hell breaking loose.

00:28:16.420 --> 00:28:21.460
So I didn't want to do the film.

00:28:21.460 --> 00:28:26.310
David Womark, who is one of
the producers of "Life of Pi"--

00:28:26.310 --> 00:28:29.160
he was kind of--

00:28:29.160 --> 00:28:30.040
he was after me.

00:28:30.040 --> 00:28:33.750
He somehow-- I think all
American producers are

00:28:33.750 --> 00:28:37.020
very, very good at convincing
people, the actors.

00:28:37.020 --> 00:28:40.380
So he somehow convinced
me to do this film.

00:28:40.380 --> 00:28:42.820
But I'm happy that
I'm part of it.

00:28:42.820 --> 00:28:45.060
Though I don't like
myself in the film,

00:28:45.060 --> 00:28:50.490
because the character
that I played in this film

00:28:50.490 --> 00:28:55.010
is something which
gives me creeps.

00:28:55.010 --> 00:28:59.130
But yes, I'm very happy that
these two films are ready.

00:28:59.130 --> 00:29:02.070
And they are going to
take festival routes,

00:29:02.070 --> 00:29:04.660
and then they will be
releasing in India.

